Smart Cities
https://datascience.columbia.edu/smart-cities

Research conducted by the Smart Cities Center develops and monitors sustainable urban infrastructure and buildings, 
improves the power supply through smart grid technology, detects and counteracts problems with aging urban
infrastructure, calculates and communicates optimal transportation routes under congested traffic conditions,
and deploys ubiquitous sensing devices to facilitate everyday activities in a crowded urban environment. 
The Center is housed on the Morningside campus.



